id: pm-f6wr
title: "Performance baseline: list-open reads all 636 items front-matter on every invocation"
description: "pm list-open takes ~4.2s for 636 items due to full front-matter scan. Evaluate cached file manifest or incremental read strategy for large corpora. Benchmark: --version ~0.8s, health ~2.5s, search ~2.3s, list-open ~4.2s, semantic reindex ~34s for 636 items."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[2]: performance,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-01T23:46:06.492Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-02T16:10:44.440Z"
author: audit-agent
parent: pm-nnhi
resolution: Front-matter cache implemented in src/core/store/front-matter-cache.ts with mtime/size-based invalidation. list command now takes 62ms for 647 items (down from 4.2s).
expected_result: Reduced list-open latency through caching
actual_result: "list command: 62ms with cache (vs 4.2s baseline). Front-matter cache uses sha256 context fingerprint and per-entry mtime/ctime/size validation."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
