comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-02T06:48:21.552Z",audit-agent,"Audit 2026-05-02: listAllDocuments reads all files from all type directories, parses each with TOON/JSON parser, runs onRead hooks, then deduplicates by ID. For 636+ items this is O(n) reads. A manifest-based approach (tracking id->path->mtime) would enable incremental reads. Calendar listAllFrontMatter has the same issue. Sentry lazy-loading confirmed working (ensureSentryInit with _initDone guard). Embedding batch retry with exponential backoff confirmed correct."
  "2026-05-02T07:46:03.822Z",audit-agent,"2026-05-02 audit: Performance measured - list-open ~0.95s, search ~1.58s (includes Ollama), context ~1.17s, calendar ~0.74s for 644 items. Acceptable but list-open could benefit from pagination/lazy-load for very large projects (1000+ items)."
  "2026-05-02T11:52:39.102Z",audit-agent,"2026-05-02 audit note: Performance issue confirmed but mitigated by current codebase size (647 items, sub-2s response). Will become important if tracker exceeds 1000+ items. No regression since last check."
  "2026-05-02T13:04:14.460Z",agent,"Implemented persistent on-disk front-matter cache (src/core/store/front-matter-cache.ts). Cache uses mtime+size fingerprinting for incremental refresh. Context fingerprint guards against format/schema changes. Warm list-open: 61ms vs cold scan. 4 new unit tests for cache behavior."
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
